<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - LOW AIR PRESSURE WARNING LIGHT,
        CIRCUIT, CLUSTER AND ALARM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>LOW AIR PRESSURE WARNING LIGHT, CIRCUIT, CLUSTER AND ALARM</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08245x_9.xml" xrefid="x0824517">Low Air Pressure Warning Light and Alarm
                    <xref refid="x0824517"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for operation description.
            </para>
            <para>This light should come on for a bulb test during the Speedometer/Tachometer self-test process, then
                turn OFF.
            </para>
            <para>The light and alarm should be on when system air pressure is less than 60 PSI (413.7 KPa).</para>
            <para>If the light works but not the alarm, skip Steps 1 and 8. If the alarm works but not the light, skip
                Steps 9 through 12.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Low Air Pressure Warning Light, Switches, Circuit, Cluster and Alarm</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Vehicle air pressure must be less than 60 PSI (413.7 KPa) for this test.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0824528">
                <title>Testing Low Air Pressure Warning Light, Switches, Circuit, Cluster and Alarm</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.23in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove bulb and test.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Bulb connectors.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Re-install bulb and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace bulb.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove cluster connector (72). Measure voltage to ground at circuit 28A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 28A, to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 28A/ 13D from 10A fuse F4-A, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Disconnect connectors (678) and (679) from low air pressure switches. With less
                                    than 60 PSI (413.7 KPa) air pressure, measure resistance across switch terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Switch terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace the low air pressure switch and go to the next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (678) measure resistance to ground at circuit 40-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(678), 40-GA to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 40-GA/11-GLB, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (679) measure resistance to ground at circuit 40-GB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(679), 40-GB to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 40-GB/11-GLB, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (72) measure resistance to ground at circuit 40C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 40C to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 40C/40A/40B, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector. (678) use a test lead to jumper circuit 40A to cir. 40-GA. At
                                    connector (72) measure resistance to ground at circuit 40C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 40C, to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Remove jumper, go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 40C/40A between connector (72) and
                                    primary low air switch, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (679) use a test lead to jumper circuit 40B to circuit 40-GB. At
                                    connector (72) measure resistance to ground at circuit 40C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 40C to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Remove jumper, and reconnect connector. (678) and (679). Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 40C/40B between connector (72) and
                                    secondary low air switch, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>With a good bulb installed, measure resistance between cluster (72) cavity 6 and
                                    cavity 5
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), cavity 6 to cavity 5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Light path in cluster tests good. Go to next step if alarm still does not work.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open circuit in cluster. Replace the gauge cluster. Go to next step if alarm still
                                    does not work.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>10.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (434). At connector (434) measure resistance to ground at
                                    circuit 40.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(434), 40 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in connector (434) or circuit 40, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>11.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (434) use test lead to jumper circuit 40 ground. At (434) measure
                                    resistance to ground at circuit 40.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(434), 40 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Remove jumper and reconnect (434). Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 40, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>12.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (434), measure voltage to ground at circuit 28C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(434), 28C to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 28C/13D from 10A fuse F4-A, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>13.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Jumper connector (72) circuit 40 to ground. Does alarm sound?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), 40 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace alarm.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>14.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster (72) cavity 17 and cavity 5
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824519">(Figure 19)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(72), cavity 17 (+) to cavity 5 (-).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;3 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Alarm path in cluster tests good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open circuit in cluster. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
